This is a "work in progress" project, developed as a Google Summer of Code 2009 project.

Name: XWiki Integration With Open Office
Author: Cristina Scheau
Mentor: Sergiu Dumitriu
Website: http://gsoc.myxwiki.org/xwiki/bin/view/XWiki+Integration+With+Open+Office/

How to build and install the project:
1. Download and install OpenOffice.org 3. from http://www.openoffice.org/
2. Download and install OpenOffice SDK 3. from http://download.openoffice.org/3.1.0/sdk.html
3. Download the CVS project http://api.openoffice.org/source/browse/api/maven2integration/ and run mvn install in order to install the maven open office plugin in the local repository
4. Enter in the root folder of the XOO project and run
mvn install
5. In the target folder there is an archive xoo-1.0-bin.zip. This is the extension. In order to install it run:
 [<OfficePath>/program] $ unopkg add --shared xoo-1.0-bin.zip
Another method to install the extension is:
OppenOffice.org Writer -> Tools -> Extension Manager -> Add -> Browse to the path of the zip file xoo-1.0-bin.zip
Restart the Writer. A new menu XWiki should be enabled.

You can find more details at: http://gsoc.myxwiki.org/xwiki/bin/view/XWiki+Integration+With+Open+Office/How+to+build+and+install+XOO
